The paper deals with error control in network coding, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of matrix and subspace perspectives suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the signal processing (cs.SI) sub-category. The paper proposes a decoding algorithm that involves partial information about errors, which could be relevant to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on error correction and decoding suggests that it may also be relevant to the computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-category.
